<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="95" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1451,1766]" pageId="3" pageNumber="95">
In a revision of the tribe 
<taxonomicName box="[420,512,1452,1478]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Cacteae">Cacteae</taxonomicName>
, subtribe 
<taxonomicName authority="Doweld" authorityName="Doweld" authorityYear="1998" box="[622,883,1451,1477]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Sclerocactinae">Sclerocactinae Doweld</taxonomicName>
of the 
<taxonomicName box="[964,1077,1452,1478]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Cactaceae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Doweld, A. B." box="[1093,1251,1451,1478]" pageId="3" pageNumber="95" pagination="15 - 30" refId="ref4663" refString="Doweld, A. B. (1998) Konspekt filogeneticheskoj sistemy triby Cacteae (Cactoideae - Cactaceae). I. Sistema podtrib Sclerocactinae - Bravocactinae - Turbinicarpinae [An outline of the phylogenetic system of classification of the tribe Cacteae (Cactoideae - Cactaceae). I. System of the subtribes Sclerocactinae - Bravocactinae - Turbinicarpinae]. Sukkulenty / Succulents (Moscow) 1998 (1): 15 - 30. [In Russian]" type="journal article" year="1998">Doweld 1998</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Doweld, A. B." box="[1263,1323,1452,1478]" pageId="3" pageNumber="95" pagination="111 - 123" refId="ref4743" refString="Doweld, A. B. (2000) Obzor triby Cacteae (Cactaceae). Rody i nadrodovye taksony: 1. (Conspectus systematis tribus Cacteae (Cactaceae). Genera et taxa supragenerici: 1.) Novosti sistematiki vysshikh rastenij 32: 111 - 123. 2000. [In Russian]" type="journal article" year="2000">2000</bibRefCitation>
), the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Britton &amp; Rose (1922)" authorityName="Britton &amp; Rose" authorityYear="1922" box="[136,511,1487,1514]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Toumeya" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[136,236,1488,1513]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="95">Toumeya</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Britton, N. L. &amp; Rose, J. N." box="[247,511,1487,1514]" pageId="3" pageNumber="95" pagination="3" refId="ref4217" refString="Britton, N. L. &amp; Rose, J. N. (1922) The Cactaceae, descriptions and illustrations of plants of the Cactus family. Vol. 3. Carnegie Institution, Washington. [The Carnegie Institution of Washington Publication 248, Vol. 3] [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 32127275]" type="book chapter" year="1922">Britton &amp; Rose (1922)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was accepted as a distinct genus on the basis of the comprehensive complex of characters, including newly added seed micromorphology in particular. However, the parahomonym was known at that time, and Doweld (
<emphasis box="[401,461,1559,1585]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="95">in litt</emphasis>
.) submitted an official request to the General Committee of Botanical Nomenclature for the binding decision whether the pair of parahomonyms, 
<taxonomicName authority="Britton &amp; Rose (1922)" authorityName="Britton &amp; Rose" authorityYear="1922" box="[779,1140,1595,1622]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Toumeya" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[779,879,1596,1621]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="95">Toumeya</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Britton, N. L. &amp; Rose, J. N." box="[886,1140,1595,1622]" pageId="3" pageNumber="95" pagination="3" refId="ref4217" refString="Britton, N. L. &amp; Rose, J. N. (1922) The Cactaceae, descriptions and illustrations of plants of the Cactus family. Vol. 3. Carnegie Institution, Washington. [The Carnegie Institution of Washington Publication 248, Vol. 3] [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 32127275]" type="book chapter" year="1922">Britton &amp; Rose (1922)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="W. H. Harvey (1858)" authorityName="W. H. Harvey" authorityYear="1858" class="Florideophyceae" family="Batrachospermaceae" genus="Tuomeya" kingdom="Plantae" order="Nemaliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="95" phylum="Rhodophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1196,1297,1596,1621]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="95">Tuomeya</emphasis>
W.H. 
<bibRefCitation author="Harvey, W. H." pageId="3" pageNumber="95" refId="ref5145" refString="Harvey, W. H. (1858) Nereis boreali-americana; or, contributions towards a history of the marine algae of the atlantic and pacific coasts of North America. Part 3. for the Smithsonian Institution, Washington. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 48974738]" type="url" year="1858">Harvey (1858)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, are sufficiently alike to be confused. The Committee for Spermatophyta resolved the case and confirmed that these generic names are homonyms (
<bibRefCitation author="Brummitt, R. K." box="[547,781,1667,1694]" pageId="3" pageNumber="95" pagination="813 - 825" refId="ref4282" refString="Brummitt, R. K. (2004) Report of the Committee for Spermatophyta: 54. Taxon 53: 813 - 825. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 4135458" type="journal article" year="2004">Brummitt 2004: 824</bibRefCitation>
), and the General Committee approved this decision (
<bibRefCitation author="Barrie, F. R." pageId="3" pageNumber="95" pagination="795 - 800" refId="ref4183" refString="Barrie, F. R. (2006) Report of the General Committee: 9. Taxon 55: 795 - 800. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 25065657" type="journal article" year="2006">Barrie 2006: 798</bibRefCitation>
). In this connection, a new replacement name for cacti is validated here in anticipation of the preparing new revision of the systematics of the tribe 
<taxonomicName box="[571,663,1740,1766]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Cacteae">Cacteae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
